# id: ChannelInterceptor -> boolean preReceive(MessageChannel channel)_
commentText: Invoked as soon as receive is called and before a Message is_actually retrieved. If the return value is 'false', then no_Message will be retrieved. This only applies to PollableChannels.
codeText: boolean preReceive(MessageChannel channel)_

# id: ChannelInterceptor -> Message<?> preSend(Message<?> message, MessageChannel channel)_
commentText: Invoked before the Message is actually sent to the channel._This allows for modification of the Message if necessary._If this method returns null, then the actual_send invocation will not occur.

# id: ChannelInterceptor -> void afterReceiveCompletion(Message<?> message, MessageChannel channel, Exception ex)_
commentText:
Invoked after the completion of a receive regardless of any exception that_have been raised thus allowing for proper resource cleanup._

Note that this will be invoked only if preReceive successfully_completed and returned {@code true}._@since 4.1
codeText: void afterReceiveCompletion(Message<?> message, MessageChannel channel, Exception ex)_

# id: ChannelInterceptor -> void afterSendCompletion(Message<?> message, MessageChannel channel, boolean sent, Exception ex)_
commentText:
Invoked after the completion of a send regardless of any exception that_have been raised thus allowing for proper resource cleanup._

Note that this will be invoked only if preSend successfully completed_and returned a Message, i.e. it did not return {@code null}._@since 4.1
codeText: void afterSendCompletion(Message<?> message, MessageChannel channel, boolean sent, Exception ex)_
